half-pie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:imperfect; half-way; (neither one thing nor the other); mediocre (sometimes used to express an unsatisfactory incompleteness), (cf. its neither my arse nor John Jackson's); or else (of mechanical things) merely = `half' cf 1950 quotation.  [poss. from Ma. pai good]. Half-and-half; half-way; (neither one thing nor the other); mediocre (sometimes used to express an unsatisfactory incompleteness), (cf. its neither my arse nor John Jackson's); or else (of mechanical things) merely = `half' cf 1950 quotation.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (informal
